The paper deals with image denoising, which is a common problem in computer vision and image processing. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses statistical shrinkage and estimation, which are topics in information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper proposes a new approach to selecting center pixel weights, which involves tuning the weights for each image pixel, making it relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed method using peak signal and noise ratio (PSNR) and structural similarity (SSIM), which are metrics commonly used in signal processing (cs.SI).
